Large flower heads produce soft pink blooms on shorter, sturdier stems than other varieties. Attracts beneficial, pollinating insects & butterflies. 12" x 16"
Forms a low carpet of tiny round powdery blue-grey leaves, accented by tiny white flower clusters. 2-4" x 8-12"

Striking silver foliage with yellow toothed edges that mature to a cream edge by fall. A silvery crown of soft pink buds open to reveal shell-pink starry flower heads that deepen to magenta. Upright habit. 12"T x 16"W

Light blue-green leaves edged in white. Large clusters of dainty pale pink flowers. 
15-18"T x 12"W
Forms a low, blue-green carpet. Foliage may take on a reddish tinge during the colder months. Small white flowers in summer attract butterflies. 1-2"T x 8"W
Small, scalloped green leaves form a durable, weed smothering groundcover. Small pink flowers create a layer of color over the lush carpet of foliage. 2"T x 6-12"W

Low growing with vivid, lime-green leaves. 
2-4"T 12-24"W

Unique low, cascading habit with clump, dark pink-tinged foliage. Very attractive for mixed containers. Can be a houseplant; 
6"T x 18-36"W

Brilliant chartreuse-yellow needle-like foliage which turns orange in the cooler season. 
3-6"T x 2-3'W
Thick, round, blue-green, scalloped foliage edged with a deep pink line; turns all pink in fall. 6-12"T x 12"W
Brilliant silvery leaves take on an attractive purplish tinge in cool weather. Clusters of tiny yellow flowers. 2-4"T x 24"W
Rich, deep mahogany-red leaves and glowing rosy-red flowers provide bold, contrasting color. 4-6"T x 24"W

Purple-tinted green leaves on red stems provide the ideal backdrop for the pink buds that open to green-centered white flowers. 
12-18"T x 18-24"W
Blue-gray leaves on upright, clumping stems hold showy pink flowers, which attract butterflies and bees.  12-18"T x same

Mat forming foliage turns a showy bronze and burgundy color in fall. Its trailing stems hold round leaves that form rosettes at the tips. 
3"T x 12"W
Blue-green foliage turning to deep burgundy. Dusky-pink flowers create a beautiful contrast which attracts butterflies. 9-12"T x 2-4'W

Rich rosy-pink flowers age to a coppery red atop the sturdy stems. An improvement over the popular 'S. Autumn Joy' with deeper, longer lasting flowers and hardier, sturdier stems. Use for fresh or dried arrangements. 2'T x 18"W
Unique gray-green rosettes with fine web-like hairs. Vibrant magenta flowers add an exotic touch. 4"T x 12"W
Tiny gray-green rosettes are covered with fine cobweb-like hairs. Foliage flushes red in spring; deep pink flowers appear in summer. 4"T x 12"W
Fleshy leaves that form multiples of apple-green rosettes. 4-6"T x 12"W
Emerald green leaves with deep red centers. 3-4"T x 12"W

Striking blue-gray, pencil-like, slightly curved leaves point upward and form a dense mat making an attractive groundcover or unique container plant. Can be a houseplant. 
2'T x 2-3'W

During the warm months small, deep purple flowers with a yellow center. A fast growing shrub. If kept as a container tropical outside in the summer, keep in full sun and stay on top of watering. Can be a houseplant

This shrubby drought tolerant perennial features showy coral-colored flowers in loose clusters; and soft, fuzzy gray-green foliage. Often blooms year-round in mild winter climates. Adored by hummingbirds. A great choice for waterwise beds, borders, containers and as an annual in the colder regions. 2-3'T x same
Dark green, leathery evergreen foliage with clusters of fragrant pure white tubular flowers. A favorite of florists for wedding bouquets. Can be a houseplant

A beautiful evergreen woody vine or sprawling shrub. Self-clinging branches can be sheared to a shrub form. Showy trumpet-shaped flowers appear in clusters. Great for seashore locations and accents. Can be a houseplant. 6-8' or more x vining stems 15-20' long.

This tough performer has gray-green leaves with silvery-white undersides that shimmer in the sunlight. Blue flowers are a darker blue than other Germanders. Tolerates poor, rocky soils, performs best in well-drained soils. Use as an annual in colder regions 4-6'T x same

Exceptional new variety with intense, yellow-gold foliage. Better than others, because it holds its bright color year-round and thrives in summer heat without burning. Tight, upright pyramidal form becomes conical with age. Excellent garden specimen or hedging shrub. Evergreen. 8'T x 4'W in 10 years; to 20' tall with age.
A shorter growing arborvitae that has shown better deer browsing resistance.5-7'Tx2-3'W
Fragrant clusters of white flowers on this beautiful tropical vine; can be a houseplant

Brilliant, nearly fluorescent pink flowers packed into tapered spikes emerge from dense clumps, providing fantastic summer color. Spot into rock gardens, borders, containers, or other sunny spots in the landscape. Excellent cut flower. Plant in mass for best impact. Clumps reach 6 to 8 in. tall, 18 to 20 in. wide; bloom spikes to 10 to 12 in. tall.

A superb groundcover for the rock garden, edging paths or cascading over rocks or walls. Dense, fast spreading growth suppresses weeds and tolerates light foot traffic. A profusion of blue-violet flowers cover the plant in spring. Performs through cold, heat, humidity and drought when established. 2-3'T x 18-30"W
Same as Tidal Pool only with white flowers

Tall and dramatic, purple-red flower spikes make this an exceptional choice for adding a vertical accent to the middle or back of the border or cutting garden. An exceptionally long bloom season begins in early summer. Foliage takes on deep purplish-red hues in cool weather, extending interest into fall. Clumps reach 18-22"T x 12-16"W

A highly fragrant, fast growing summer blooming vine with curled flowers resembling a snail's shell, in distinctive shades of lavender, white and creamy yellow. Can be a houseplant. Twining stems 15-20'Long
